data.name: TXT_TEMPLATE_4
data.value: - best suited for low res landscape - generated geometry can be modified easier - generated vertices will stay on grid - semi seamless texture mapping by default

data.name: TXT_MOREINFO
data.value: For more information, turn off auto close in settings.

data.name: TXT_TEMPLATE_5
data.value: - suited for high res terrain and architecture - completely seamless texture mapping - generated vertices will most likely have floating point positions

data.name: TXT_TEMPLATE_2
data.value: - suited for rare objects (e.g. unique eyecatchers) - fully seamless texture mapping - high polygon usage

data.name: TXT_NO_LOG_FILE_FOUND
data.value: No Log found in root dir!

data.name: TXT_TEMPLATE_3
data.value: - allows for highly complex input brushwork (recreate input brushes when errors occur) - will cut any solid entity (point-entities will be removed) - worldbrushes will be ignored - currently only available for the circle framework

data.name: TXT_TEMPLATE_1
data.value: - suited for common objects and architecture - relatively low polygone usage - positions of generated vertices will contain floating point numbers per default

data.name: TXT_SPECIFY_M2C_EXE
data.value: Please specify Map2Curve.exe location in Settings tab first!

data.name: TXT_TEMP_ConcreteWalk
data.value: - showcases "mapcarve" setting (new in v0.82) - enables for arcs with a radius smaller than the depth of the original brushwork (Y-axis size) - requires negative offset to have an effect
